Interface Belt.SourceOperator<In,Out>

Type Parameters:
In - the upstream element type
Out - the downstream element type
All Known Subinterfaces:
Belt.SourceToStepOperator<In,Out>
Enclosing class:
Belt
Functional Interface:
This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.
@FunctionalInterface public static interface Belt.SourceOperator<In,Out>
Represents an operation on an upstream Source that produces a downstream Source.

This is a functional interface whose functional method is compose(Source).

  • Method Details

    • compose

      Belt.Source<Out> compose(Belt.Source<? extends In> upstream)
      Connects the upstream source before this operator. Returns a downstream source.
      Parameters:
      upstream - the upstream source
      Returns:
      the downstream source
      Implementation Requirements
      The downstream source is generally expected to internally delegate to the upstream source in some way. This allows for transforming elements or signals as they travel from upstream to downstream.
